YSFON boss lauds sponsors at 57     Chelsea hit Southampton for six     Lewandowski scores late Bayern winner from spot   Former Crotone striker, Simeon Nwankwo who notched 20 goals in the 2020-21 season, is the record holder. The Super Eagles attacker however displaced Obafemi Martins to occupy the second spot with the goal he scored yesterday. The former Lille striker was Joint second Nigerian with Martins before the defeat to Fiorentina. Obagoal who has now dropped to the third spot scored 11 goals from 31 games in the 2004/05 season to help the Nerazzurri finish third. Osimhen took his tally to 12 goals in 21 appearances this season when he netted once in Napoli’s 3-2 defeat to Fiorentina last weekend, to move a goal above Martins’ performance in the 2004/05 league season. The former Golden Eaglets hitman has eight goals more between now and the end of the season to try and equal the feat set by Nwankwo last season. So far this season, the 23-year-old has scored 16 times and made five assists in 26 games in all competitions compared to the 2020/21 season, when he only managed 10 goals and three assists in 30 games across all competitions. Other Nigerians who have made career headways with their goals included Obinna Nsofor who scored six goals in 26 games in the 2005-06 season. He got 14 goals altogether from 69 Serie A games.